Building an arena for chatbots typically involves creating a virtual space where chatbots can interact with each other and with users. There are several ways to do this, including using chatbot-specific platforms, building a custom platform, or using an existing messaging platform like Facebook Messenger or Slack. Some popular chatbot-specific platforms include Platform.AI, Dialogflow, and Alice.

If you're planning to build a custom platform, you'll want to make sure to consider factors like scalability, security, and compatibility with different messaging platforms. You may also want to consider building a user interface to help users interact with the chatbots on your platform.

You will also need to set up the necessary infrastructure to host your platform, including a server and any necessary programming languages or frameworks.

Overall, building an arena for chatbots requires a good understanding of chatbot technology and the needs of your users. It may be helpful to consult with chatbot experts and user experience designers to ensure that your platform is user-friendly and effective.

Parallelizing a neural network involves distributing the computation and training process across multiple processors or nodes in a parallel computing system, such as a cluster or GPUs. To parallelize a neural network, you will need to:

1. Dissect your neural network into smaller units of computation, such as layers or activation functions.
2. Identify which of these units of computation can be parallelized efficiently.
3. Distribute the computation across multiple processors or nodes using a suitable parallel computing library or framework, such as TensorFlow or PyTorch.
4. Monitor the progress and performance of the parallelized network to ensure that it is running efficiently.

Once you have parallelized your neural network, you may need to adjust the training parameters, such as the learning rate, to prevent divergence and ensure that the parallelized network converges to the same solution as the sequential network.

Keep in mind that parallelizing a neural network is not a straightforward process, and the specific techniques and libraries needed may vary depending on the specific deep learning model and the parallel computing system you are using.
